# PRD 09–18 Implementation Analysis: RAG Pipeline Integration

> Deep scan of `nutrition-backend-b2c` (Backend), `nutrib2c-frontend` (Frontend), and `rag-pipeline-hybrid-reterival` (RAG API) — performed 2026-03-04.

---

## Executive Summary

The RAG pipeline integration across all three repos is **substantially implemented**. The foundational infrastructure (PRD-09) is in production shape. The four core feature endpoints in the RAG API are functional. Backend service files are all wired to [ragClient.ts](file:///c:/Users/Sourav%20Patil/Desktop/ASM/B2C/nutrition-backend-b2c/server/services/ragClient.ts). Frontend components exist for search, feed, meal plan, scanner, substitutions, and chatbot surfaces.

**However, 4 of the 8 RAG API endpoints specified in the PRDs are NOT implemented**, along with missing data-layer automation (PG→Neo4j sync, GraphSAGE training). These gaps prevent full end-to-end integration for ~4 features.

